track_notes: Easy hike over well maintained trails, the last 0.2 miles is a bit tough, but not a showstopper.
This was a night hike so I parked outside the Phoenix Sonoran Desert Preserve (gate closes 7pm).  I took a short wrong turn down Desert Tortoise trail.  This is an easy wide trail.
track_title: Union Hills via Dixie Loop Trail

track_notes: This route is well-maintained trail the whole way and has sections that are quite flat.  I chose to do an out-and-back to Union Hills first then turn up to Union Hills North.  However a shorter hike would be to take the V Trail shortcut across - that trail would likely have been a better choice but I was unsure at the time.  Park at Phoenix Sonoran Preserve.  Note that this is a popular urban trail system with hikers, bikers, and horses and it is busy, even on weekdays, you probably will be aharing the summit with others.
track_title: Union Hills and Union Hills North Double Activation
